@NODE "datasheet" "layout_gc/datasheet (information)"


    NAME
        layout.gadget-- An automatic GUI layout arrangement gadget.

    SUPERCLASS
        gadgetclass

    REQUIRES
        bevel.image

    DESCRIPTION
        The layout gadget is used to automatically calculate the
        positions and sizes of BOOPSI gadgets and images in a resizable
        window. Instead of handling the positions of gadgets by hand,
        you can just describe your window layout in a hierarchical
        fashion, and the layout gadget will do the rest.

        The basic method of layout of a group is as follows:
        - Calculate the minimum and maximum size of each gadget.
        - Calculate the weight totals for the group. Substract the size
          of the fixed size (weighted size 0) gadgets from the total
          size of the group.
        - Distribute the remaining space in the group according to the
          relative weighs of the children.
        - If extra space remains, distribute it evenly between the
          children.

        PRIVATE METHODS
                LAYOUT_ACTIVATEOBJECT -- Used by @{"ActivateLayoutGadget()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/layout_gc/ActivateLayoutGadget"}, sets
                the handleinput path to a gadget somewhere in a layout hierarchy.

                LAYOUT_TABCYCLE -- Sets the gadget attributes based on the
                gadget in the end of the handleinput path.

                LAYOUT_FIRSTCYCLE -- Sets the handleinput path to the first tab
                cycle gadget in a layout hierarchy.

                LAYOUT_LASTCYCLE -- Sets the handleinput path to the last tab
                cycle gadget in a layout hierarchy.

                LAYOUT_FLUSHDOMAINS -- Flushes all domain caches below a certain
                level.

                LAYOUT_FINDKEY -- Find a gadget with a key in the CommKey list.

                LAYOUT_FINDACTIVE -- Find the active gadget pointer.

                LAYOUT_FINDHELP -- Find the last gadget that returned helphit.

    METHODS
        @{"GM_HANDLEINPUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 308} -- Passed to the currently active child

        @{"GM_DOMAIN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 323} -- Passed to all children

        @{"GM_RENDER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 302} -- Passed to all children When invoked
            by @{"input.device" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/input/MAIN"}, the stack is first swapped to provide
            more workspace.

        @{"GM_LAYOUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 318} -- Passed to all children after first setting
            their size and position with @{"SetAttrs" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/SetAttrsA"}. When invoked
            by @{"input.device" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/input/MAIN"}, the stack is first swapped to provide
            more workspace.

        @{"GM_HITTEST" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 298} -- Passed to the child in whose domain
            rectangle the pointer is

        @{"GM_HELPTEST" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 314} -- Passed to the child in whose domain
            rectangle the pointer is

        @{"GM_GOACTIVE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 305} -- Passed to the currently "active" child (one
            that returned @{"GM_HITTEST" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 298})

        @{"GM_GOINACTIVE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 311} -- Passed to the currently active child

        @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65} -- Passed to superclass after scanning the
            taglist for layout specific tags

        @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70} -- Passed to superclass after scanning the
            taglist for layout specific tags

        @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66} -- Passed to superclass for non-layout tags

        @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63} -- Passed to superclass, then adding all the
            children on the taglist to the private list.

        @{"OM_DISPOSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 64} -- Passed to all children (thus disposing all
            of them), then to superclass.

        @{"GM_CLIPRECT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/reaction/reaction_class.h/File" 33} -- Passed to all children.

        @{"DTM_PROCLAYOUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/File" 288} -- Like @{"GM_LAYOUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 318}, but passes @{"DTM_PROCLAYOUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/File" 288}
            forward. Useful if the layout group contains only
            datatype objects.

        All other methods are passed to the superclass.

  ATTRIBUTES
      Attributes global to the whole layout group. Pass all of these
      BEFORE adding child objects:

      @{"GA_ReadOnly" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 189} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          Disables input to the entire layout group and its chidren.
          This tag is @{"NOT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1500} propagated to children. The input blocking
          occurs within the layout object itself.

          Defaults to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

      @{"GA_Disabled" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 78} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          Disables entire layout group and its chidren. This tag
          is propagated all children. When setting/clearing this
          tag, take care to re-set/re-clear any children you want
          included from this mass disabling ability.

          Defaults to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70})

      @{"GA_TextAttr" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 185} (@{"struct TextAttr" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/graphics/text.h/File" 65} *)
          The font that will be used for the group label.

          Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101} (uses rastport default font).

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63})

      @{"LAYOUT_Orientation" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 54} (@{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52})
          Whether the objects of this group are arranged horizontally or
          vertically. Possible values are LORIENT_HORIZONTAL and
          LORIENT_VERTICAL.

          Defaults to LORIENT_HORIZONTAL.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

      @{"LAYOUT_FixedHoriz" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 58} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          Whether the width of this layout group is fixed to the width
          assigned by the window or parent layout group. If set to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98},
          the gadget will minimize its width to the smallest possible
          value. Generally you will have to also set @{"LAYOUT_ShrinkWrap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 71}
          (below) to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95} also. It is recommended that this tag is used
          only in the top layout group. Using a weighted width of 0 gives
          more predictable results elsewhere.

          Defaults to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

      @{"LAYOUT_FixedVert" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 59} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          Whether the height of this layout group is fixed to the height
          assigned by the window or parent layout group. If set to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98},
          the gadget will minimize its height to the smallest possible
          value. Generally you will have to also set @{"LAYOUT_ShrinkWrap" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 71}
          (below) to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95} also. It is recommended that this tag is used
          only in the top layout group. Using a weighted height of 0 gives
          more predictable results elsewhere.

          Defaults to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

      @{"LAYOUT_HorizAlignment" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 63} (@{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52})
          The horizontal alignment of the objects in this layout group.
          Possible values are @{"LALIGN_LEFT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 339}, @{"LALIGN_RIGHT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 340}, and
