      @{"LAYOUT_Parent" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 147} (Object *)
          Set automatically by layout.gadget for all child objects, this
          attribute points to the parent layout object. If @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}, the
          layout object is the window's topmost layout.
          When an object is added to the layout hierarchy, it will
          receive this tag in @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}. If you so wish, you may use this to
          let the gadget talk to its parent layout group.
          Any group gadget that should work with layout.gadget must
          support this attribute.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

      @{"LAYOUT_DeferLayout" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 152} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
          By setting this tag to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95} in your window's top layout, you
          can defer the layout and refresh process off the @{"input.device" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/input/MAIN"}
          context to your application. This will make @{"input.device" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/input/MAIN"} more
          responsive, and drop the (possibly quite heavy) process of
          recalculating the display to normal application priority
          instead of the priority 20
          of @{"input.device" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/input/MAIN"}. Input handling will be retained in @{"input.device" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/input/MAIN"}
          context, to keep the GUI responsive.
          If you use this tag, you must listen to @{"LAYOUT_RequestLayout" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 157}
          and @{"LAYOUT_RequestRefresh" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 163} notifications and process them in
          prompt manner, or your GUI will not display properly, if at all.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

      @{"LAYOUT_RequestLayout" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 157} (Object *)
          If the above @{"LAYOUT_DeferLayout" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 152} tag is set to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}, the gadget
          will defer @{"GM_LAYOUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 318} methods invoked by @{"input.device" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/input/MAIN"} and notify
          its IC target with this tag. You should be listening to it in
          your application IDCMP handler (@{"IDCMP_IDCMPUPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 856}) and calling
          @{"RethinkLayout" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/layout_gc/RethinkLayout"} with @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98} for refresh flag when receiving one.

          Defaults to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}.

          Applicability is (@{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69})

      @{"LAYOUT_RequestRefresh" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 163} (Object *)
          If the above @{"LAYOUT_DeferLayout" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/gadgets/layout.h/File" 152} tag is set to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}, the gadget
          will defer @{"GM_RENDER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 302} methods invoked by @{"input.device" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/input/MAIN"} and notify
          its IC target with this tag. You should be listening to it in
